// pancake-sign — code-signing service.
//
// Owns the leaf cert + private key that signs UKIs (PE-format kernel
// images) and per-generation manifests. The build server delegates
// signing here over gRPC so the key never enters the build process.
//
// Trust boundary is the compose-internal network. Production deploys
// should front this with mTLS; see Phase 9.1.
//
// Endpoints:
//   SignUKI         — unsigned PE bytes in, signed PE bytes out.
//                     Internally shells out to sbsign(1).
//   SignManifest    — raw manifest bytes in, RSA-PKCS1v15-SHA256
//                     detached signature out.
//   GetSigningCert  — returns the leaf cert PEM. Operators bake the
//                     SubjectPublicKeyInfo into the initramfs;
//                     enroll the cert (or its CA chain) in UEFI db.

